article.headline: Siena 68, Manhattan 66
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Jack McClinton scored 18 points to help Siena edge Manhattan 68-66 Tuesday night. Antoine Jordan added 16 points and 10 rebounds as the Saints (4-17, 2-8 Metro Atlantic Athletic) snapped an eight-game losing streak. Brent Sniezyk grabbed 12 rebounds. Jeff Xavier scored 19 points, including five 3-pointers, for Manhattan (10-9, 5-6). CJ Anderson chipped in 15. Siena started the second half with a 16-2 run to take an eight-point lead, causing Manhattan to take its final timeout. Down 67-60 with 1:39 remaining, Manhattan rallied to close the deficit to 68-66 on consecutive 3s by Xavier. After David Ryan missed a shot at the other end, Peter Mulligan was fouled with 11 seconds left and sent to the line with a chance to tie the game. Mulligan missed both free throws, the second of which trickled out of bounds. But Siena's Tay Fisher stepped out of bounds with 2.2 seconds left to give the Jaspers a final chance. Without a timeout, Mulligan was forced into a hurried jumper that missed.
